  "notes": "Integrations covers 8 systems (§18.0). Procore-specific fields span §10.6, §11.7, §15.13.1–§15.13.6, §18.1.5, §18.1.7, §18.1.12, §18.1.13. Procore Object Link (row 17) and Curated Summary (row 18) records carry placeholder / future-reference only fields with mvpStatus: Deferred — they do not become a full Procore canonical model in Phase 1 and the no-full-Procore-mirror constraint (P-10) is preserved. Procore owns Procore-native records. PCC owns PCC-native legacy workflow replacement records and derived PCC records (curated summaries/object links/signals) with required source lineage. ProcoreCompanyId three-form contract is canonical here for the integration layer; settings family carries the surface-level forms. Sage Intacct = accounting book of record (VR-14). One field (outlook_CalendarMapping) carries fieldType 'unknown' because the contract describes a concept without specifying a concrete type; this is resolvable in Step 4 with no architecture decision."
}
